text.section:
When a risk retention group files an application for charter, the risk retention group shall provide to the Commissioner the following information:
the name of the risk retention group;
the identity of the initial members of the risk retention group;
the identity of the individuals who organized the risk retention group, or who will provide administrative services or otherwise influence or control the activities of the risk retention group;
the amount and nature of initial capitalization;
the coverages to be afforded; and
the states in which the risk retention group intends to operate.
